This debian/ directory lives under packaging/debian/debian/ in the
repository so that all Debian packaging content stays together under
packaging/debian/. To use it, overlay this directory onto a clean
checkout of upstream BYVoid/OpenCC (e.g. `cp -r packaging/debian/debian
<upstream-checkout>/debian`) and run `dpkg-buildpackage` from there.

This debian/ directory is authored against upstream BYVoid/OpenCC's file
layout at 1.4.1, and was validated by running `dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc
-b` against a clean checkout of upstream `master` (all six binary
packages build, `dh_missing --fail-missing` finds nothing unclaimed,
`ctest` passes 19/19, and `lintian --pedantic` reports no errors). It
authored strictly against the file layout present in the upstream source
tree at 1.4.1 — building it against any checkout that contains files
beyond what upstream ships will cause dh_missing to fail on those extra
files.

Known gaps in this recreation of the Debian packaging flow (not a full
archive-ready upload):

- This mirrors and rebases exactly the four patches in debian/patches/
  (0003, 0004, 0005, 0009) — that is the complete set upstream currently
  mirrors from Debian's series, not a partial one; see
  packaging/debian/README.md.
- No orig tarball repack (Files-Excluded / "+ds1") is implemented.
  A real upload would strip deps/marisa-0.3.1, deps/rapidjson-1.1.0,
  deps/tclap-1.2.5, and deps/googletest-1.15.0 (all replaced by
  USE_SYSTEM_* build options; see debian/rules) from the .orig tarball.
  deps/darts-clone-0.32h and plugins/jieba/deps/cppjieba have no system
  package to build against and would stay bundled either way. See the
  per-directory comments in debian/copyright.
- debian/libopencc-data.install and debian/opencc-jieba.install hardcode
  the *.json config filenames rather than globbing, to keep the two
  packages' shared usr/share/opencc/*.json directory unambiguous. Keep
  this list in sync with the CONFIG_FILES list in data/CMakeLists.txt
  and the json list in plugins/jieba/CMakeLists.txt when configs are
  added or renamed.
- No debian/libopencc1.4.symbols file yet: dh_makeshlibs generates a
  shlibs file automatically, which is enough for ${shlibs:Depends}, but
  a real upload should add a proper symbols file for finer-grained
  dependency versioning.
- Binary packages are recreated to validate the build end-to-end; they
  are not built with reproducible/archive build flags (e.g. no
  buildinfo/signing setup) and have not been uploaded anywhere.
